// =====================================================
// ui_import_material_code — bulk-import product.fk_main_fabric_code from an
// uploaded CSV file (2 columns: code, material_code).
//
// SANDBOX NOTE: this environment's SES lockdown blocks quite a lot of normal
// browser API surface: document.* property access, fetch(), writing to any
// global (e.g. window.XLSX), and `new FileReader()` all throw. That rules
// out loading a binary .xlsx parser (SheetJS) entirely — there's no way to
// fetch one in, and no way to read the file's bytes even if there were. So:
//   - Mounting follows ui_material_out's pattern: antd Modal.confirm() with
//     OK/Cancel hidden, custom buttons inside `content`, Modal.destroyAll()
//     to close.
//   - Files are read via Blob.prototype.text() on the File object antd's
//     Upload already hands us (an instance method on an existing object,
//     not a global we're instantiating — this one is allowed) and parsed as
//     plain delimited text (comma/semicolon/tab, auto-detected). Convert
//     .xlsx/.xls to CSV before uploading.
//
// Stored as a `source_code` row named 'ui_import_material_code'.
// Loaded via loadCode(ctx, 'ui_import_material_code'); compiled with
// new Function('React','antd','dayjs','ctx', src)(React, antd, dayjs, ctx).
//
// EXPORTS (contract):
//   openModal({ ctx, onSaved })
